result.execSummary:
The defendant Casey Ann Voneschen #258004 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Mailed to Defendant w/Appeal Rights (requested to return to COC).

01:51 PM Defendant Casey Ann Voneschen #258004 via phone pro se from Shakopee Correctional Facility in MN.  DA Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Set for Return on Warrant/Plea and Sentencing.  DA Froelich recites agreement.  Defendant pleading Guilty to County One.  State requesting 9 months incarceration, concurrent to Nicolett County, MN case 52-CR-18-33.  Restitution has been paid.  ADA David Olson enters, appears for State.  Court advises Defendant of right to be present and right to an attorney, she understands and waives.  Constitutional rights explained to Defendant.  Defendant pleads Guilty to Count One.  COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEFENDANT FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.  Court finds Defendant Guilty and adjudicates.  ADA Olson makes statement.  Defendant makes statement.  Court quashes warrant.  Court sentences Defendant to 9 months in PCJ, concurrent to Nicolett County case 52-CR-18-33.  Defendant may serve time in Shakopee Correctional Facility, MN.  Court costs waived.  Appeal rights given.  Court questions release date.  11/2021 unless she completes program.  Court orders Defendant to report to PJC w/in 30 days of release for DNA and photos/prints.  Adjourned at 2:09 PM
Return on warrant on July 11, 2019 at 01:15 pm.
Plea hearing on July 11, 2019 at 01:15 pm.
Plea hearing on July 9, 2019 at 02:00 pm.
